  schema:name "How Plants Defend Themselves" ;
  schema:description "Explanation of plant defense strategies as active, multi-layered systems: physical barriers, constitutive and induced chemical defenses, volatile signaling, and the coevolutionary arms race between plants and herbivores" ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-04-02" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-04-02" ;
  emsenn:Addresses "Why plants are green but not eaten; how plants communicate damage through chemistry; why cabbage white caterpillars can eat brassicas when other insects cannot; how companion planting exploits plant defense" ;
